question.query: what projects are trending on base and solana

steps.text:
Short answer (snapshot as of today — 2026-01-13):

Base (Coinbase L2) — trending projects / narratives
- Zora / creator coins on Base — creator-token launches on Zora (e.g., the Nick Shirley token) have been a hot / controversial topic recently. (source: CoinTelegraph)
- BasePerp — on‑chain perpetuals / perp DEX activity on Base is getting attention (and new integrations). Example: partnerships bringing AI data to BasePerp. (source: Medium / project posts)
- Coinbase ecosystem pushes — Coinbase’s 2026 roadmap and “everything exchange” posture is driving attention and flows into Base-native apps. (source: CoinTelegraph)
- General narrative: increasing interest in on‑chain derivatives, creator-economy tokens and L2-native tooling on Base (perp DEXs, bridges, creator marketplaces).

Solana — trending projects / narratives
- Solana Mobile / SKR token — Solana Mobile is launching the SKR governance/token airdrop for Seeker users (launch date announced Jan 21), which is widely discussed. (sources: Decrypt, CoinTelegraph)
- Jupiter — launched JupUSD (a Solana stablecoin / on‑chain settlement token backed by BlackRock BUIDL exposures) — big news for settlement & RWA/stablecoin flows on Solana. (source: CoinTelegraph / CoinMarketCap)
- PumpSwap / memecoin frenzy — Solana memecoin trading exploded recently; PumpSwap and other DEXs saw record volumes during the memecoin surge. (source: Coindesk)
- Stablecoin / RWA activity — large inflows into Solana stablecoins and RWA-related tokens have pushed TVL and market cap movement on the chain. (source: CoinTelegraph / CoinMarketCap)
- Ongoing ecosystem staples that remain important: Jupiter (DEX aggregator), Magic Eden (NFT marketplace), Phantom (wallet), Orca/Raydium (DEX/AMM) — these show up frequently in on‑chain activity and headlines.

If you want, I can:
- Pull live leaderboards (top tokens / trending coins by 24h volume) on Base and Solana (CoinGecko / CoinMarketCap / DappRadar), or
- Give a deeper dive into any single project (metrics, tokenomics, recent on‑chain activity, risks). Which would you prefer?
